ide><article class=3D"PostLayout-module--content--2914f"><div class=3D"text=
-formatting"><div class=3D"text-formatting"><p>There are many spokes on the=
 <a href=3D"https://klientboost.com/cro/conversion-rate-optimization-strate=
gy/" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noreferrer noopener">conversion rate optimiza=
tion </a>wheel. The most underrated spoke=E2=80=94no question=E2=80=94is <a=
 href=3D"https://venngage.com/blog/how-to-choose-fonts/" target=3D"_blank" =
rel=3D"noreferrer noopener">landing page and website fonts</a>.</p><p>But w=
ho the heck cares about fonts, really?</p><p>The people looking to buy your=
 stuff, that=E2=80=99s who.&nbsp;</p><p>They may not even realize it, but t=
he fonts you choose (in combination with whitespace and imagery) impact use=
r experience (UX).&nbsp;</p><p><strong>To put it plainly, if your site look=
s sh*tty it corrodes your credibility.&nbsp;</strong></p><p>An ugly site pu=
shes people to leave as soon as they land. Google calls that a bounce, and =
it=E2=80=99s bad for your rank.&nbsp;</p><p>If a website or landing page is=
 your <a href=3D"https://klientboost.com/cro/the-hottest-startup-landing-pa=
ges-the-good-the-bad-and-the-ugly/" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noreferrer noo=
pener">company=E2=80=99s book cover</a>, <strong>fonts are the vital first =
impression</strong> when a user opens the book.</p><p>Landing page and webs=
ite fonts make your headline look good, and your headline is the hook that =
convinces a user to scroll down the page.&nbsp;</p><p>Don=E2=80=99t =F0=9F=
=91=8F ignore =F0=9F=91=8F your =F0=9F=91=8F fonts.</p><p>Don=E2=80=99t bel=
ieve me? Here=E2=80=99s proof:</p><p>Click Laboratory was ecstatic when a n=
ew software company hired them to improve their conversion rates. Instead o=
f focusing on the checkout process, the button colors, or the value proposi=
tions, Click Lab decided to<a href=3D"http://www.clicklaboratory.com/case-s=
tudies/increasing-sales-pipeline-with-adaptive-web-design/" target=3D"_blan=
k" rel=3D"noreferrer noopener"> start with the fonts</a>.</p></div><div><fi=
gure class=3D"wp-block-image"><img height=3D"143" width=3D"600" loading=3D"=
lazy" src=3D"https://wp.klientboost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/img_6100=
5dff75d21.png" alt=3D"A small difference with big impact =E2=80=93 source "=
><figcaption class=3D"wp-element-caption">A small difference with big impac=
t =E2=80=93 <a href=3D"http://marketingland.com/everything-need-know-fonts-=
conversion-optimization-100113" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noreferrer noopene=
r">source</a> </figcaption></figure></div><div class=3D"text-formatting"><p=
>The results?</p><ul><li>Exit rate decreased by 19% (that=E2=80=99s good)</=
li><li>Bounce rate decreased by 10% (that=E2=80=99s great)</li><li><strong>=
Conversion rates increased by 133% </strong>(that=E2=80=99s <em>WTF</em> aw=
esome)</li></ul><p>Remember when Steve Jobs talked about how he <a href=3D"=
http://www.telegraph.co.uk/technology/steve-jobs/8721676/Steve-Jobs-his-10-=
most-inspirational-quotes.html" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noreferrer noopene=
r">dropped out of school</a> and learned about typography?</p><blockquote c=
lass=3D"wp-block-quote"><p><em>=E2=80=9CBecause I had dropped out and didn=
=E2=80=99t have to take the normal classes, I decided to take a </em><stron=
g><em>calligraphy class</em></strong><em> to learn how to do this. I learne=
d about serif and sans serif typefaces, about varying the amount of space b=
etween different letter combinations, about what makes great typography gre=
at. It was beautiful, historical, artistically subtle in a way that science=
 can=E2=80=99t capture, and I found it fascinating.&nbsp;</em></p><p><em>No=
ne of this had even a hope of any practical application in my life. But ten=
 years later, when we were designing the first Macintosh computer, it all c=
ame back to me. And we designed it all into the Mac. It was the </em><stron=
g><em>first computer with beautiful typography</em></strong><em>.=E2=80=9D<=
/em></p></blockquote><p>They go unnoticed by most but, overall, a focus on =
web design will <a href=3D"http://www.entrepreneur.com/article/235755" targ=
et=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noreferrer noopener">improve your conversion rates</a>=
.</p><p>The fonts you use are the conversion rate <strong>details that matt=
er</strong>.</p><p>A day in the life of a font begins now.&nbsp;</p><p>By t=
he end of this post, you=E2=80=99ll know&nbsp;</p><ul><li>when to use curly=
 fonts over fonts without feet</li><li>how that differentiator affects your=
 conversion rate</li><li>where to find high-converting fonts</li><li>how to=
 install them on your site</li><li>how the schematics of a font can be the =
difference between a browser turning into a buyer or a bouncer.&nbsp;</li><=
/ul><p><em>What the font,</em> heh? Who knew.</p></div><div class=3D"TableO=
