referrer noopener">source</a></figcaption></figure></div><div class=3D"text=
-formatting"><p>If typeface and fonts work to display language in a pleasin=
g way, think of typography as more of a body language.&nbsp;</p></div><h2 i=
d=3D"h-landing-page-and-website-fonts-matter-for-conversions">Landing page =
and website fonts matter for conversions </h2><div class=3D"text-formatting=
"><p><a href=3D"https://klientboost.com/landing-pages/landing-page-examples=
/" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noreferrer noopener">Landing pages</a> and webs=
ites are built for one reason: to convert a target audience. When you desig=
n your landing page or website, you design it for that target audience.&nbs=
p;</p><p>To be clear: You don=E2=80=99t pick a typeface and font style for =
your website or landing page to evoke deep-rooted emotions or trigger some =
<strong>neurological rainbow of happiness</strong> in your visitors=E2=80=
=99 brains (although that would be sweet).</p><p><strong>The goal of your w=
ebsite font is simply to be read.</strong></p><p>But isn=E2=80=99t that the=
 goal of the landing page or website headline?</p><p>Yes. Your headline and=
 font work together.</p><p>If a headline (and the subsequent copy) gets rea=
d, it=E2=80=99s partly because it was <em>easy to read</em>.</p><p>There ha=
ve been plenty of studies (like <a href=3D"http://www.awaionline.com/2011/1=
0/the-best-fonts-to-use-in-print-online-and-email/?mode=3Dpdf" target=3D"_b=
lank" rel=3D"noreferrer noopener">this one</a>, and <a href=3D"https://thep=
roductiveengineer.net/does-font-and-font-size-affect-reading-speed/" target=
=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noreferrer noopener">this one</a>, and <a href=3D"https:=
//digitalcommons.unomaha.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=3D1072&amp;context=
=3Duniversity_honors_program#:~:text=3DComprehension%20scores%20were%20high=
er%20in,and%20memory%20in%20extended%20text." target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"nore=
ferrer noopener">this one</a>) that show that some fonts are easier to read=
 and promote better reading comprehension than others.&nbsp;</p><p>That=E2=
=80=99s what you=E2=80=99re going for.</p><p>Let=E2=80=99s say you make ska=
teboards. Your target audience is younger, you=E2=80=99re in the <a href=3D=
"http://klientboost.com/marketing/b2c-marketing" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"n=
oreferrer noopener">B2C marketing space</a>, and you sell a =E2=80=9Cfun=E2=
=80=9D product. You can use a more liberal typeface.</p></div><div><figure =
class=3D"wp-block-image"><img height=3D"684" width=3D"1600" loading=3D"lazy=
" src=3D"https://wp.klientboost.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/img_61005e07=
bfdac.png" alt=3D"This page uses a fun font called Poppins to reach a young=
er audience=E2=80=93 source"><figcaption class=3D"wp-element-caption">This =
