ven though serif fonts are more difficult to read online).</p><p><strong>Th=
e crazy thing?</strong>&nbsp;</p><p>The study proved that people who read s=
ans serif text scored higher in comprehension and reading speed.</p><p>So w=
hat=E2=80=99s more important? The perception of valuable site content by yo=
